<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Sheffield United will bring in Scotland forward Oliver Burke this week as part of a swap deal with West Bromwich Albion for Callum Robinson.</p>

<p>Burke is not required at the Hawthorns and spent the last season on-loan at Spanish side Alaves.</p>

<p>Meanwhile, Robinson spent the last season on-loan at the Hawthorns and impressed the club during their promotion winning campaign. </p>

<p>Sheffield United are close to signing West Brom's Oliver Burke in what would be a swap deal</p>

<p>It would see Callum Robinson (right) return to the Hawthorns following a loan spell last year</p>

<p>Sheffield United manager Chris Wilder is also looking to complete the £11m double signing of Derby County full-backs Jayden Bogle and Max Lowe.</p>

<p>Bogle, 20, has also had interest from West Ham and Fulham during the summer. </p>

<p>Talks are ongoing with both players left out of Derby's squad that faced Barrow in the Carabao Cup on Saturday.</p>

<p>Burke and Robinson are currently away on international duty and will finalise their transfers once they return.</p>

<p>Sheffield United are also close to signing Jayden Bogle (left) and Max Lowe from Derby</p>

<p>Meanwhile, West Brom have signed Brighton goalkeeper David Button for an undisclosed fee.</p>

<p>The Baggies confirmed the transfer this morning ahead of a pre-season friendly against the Seagulls.</p>

<p>He is expected to provide competition to number one keeper Sam Johnstone this season. </p>
